FBIS4-11945 "drnes064_r_94007" FBIS-NES-94-064 Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 India Official Denies `Deal' With LTTE To Ensure Rao's Security Official Denies `Deal' With LTTE To Ensure Rao's Security BK3003050994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 29 Mar 94 BK3003050994 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] An official spokesman in New Delhi today denied reports appearing in a section of the press that the Indian security agencies have sought an assurance from the LTTE [Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam] regarding the prime minister's security during his recent visit to Britain. He termed the reports as mischievous and baseless. The spokesman said there is absolutely no basis for reports of an alleged deal between the LTTE and the government in this regard. He said there is no question of lifting the ban on the LTTE imposed two years ago under the Unlawful Activities Prevention Act.
